    <string name="voidaisetup">VoidAI API key setup</string>
    <string name="firsttime_1">NumAI Plus brings modern LLMs (ChatGPT, DeepSeek, Gemini and more) to your old Android device.\n\nTo start, you\'ll need an API key. This app will guide you through the process. All you need is a modern smartphone or PC.\n\nThe guide will use the free VoidAI provider. If you already have an API key or use another provider, press the Skip button.</string>
    <string name="firsttime_2">1. On a modern browser, go to the following URL and create an account.\n<b>voidai.app/register</b>\nIf you use Gmail, enter your email without the dots before @gmail.com.\n2. After logging in, navigate to the <b>API Keys</b> section in your dashboard.\n3. Click <b>Generate New API Key</b>.\n4. Copy the key that appears and transfer it to your phone using one of these methods:\n\n<b>Method 1: File transfer</b>\n• Create a text file with only the API key and save it.\n• Transfer the file to your phone via USB, Bluetooth, gtrxac.fi/fh or similar.\n• You will be able to import the key from the file on the next screen.\n\n<b>Method 2: adb</b>\n• On the <b>next screen</b>, press on the text input box, and paste the key using this command:\n<b>adb shell input text API_KEY</b></string>
    <string name="hello_user">Hello, User</string>
    <string name="cloudflare_title">Android 1.0–2.2 Warning</string>
    <string name="cloudflare_msg">Website protection services such as Cloudflare block connections from Android &#60;2.3, as they consider them unsafe. Most AI platforms, including VoidAI, use such protections, so you may not be able to connect to them from your device and you have to use something else.\n\n<b>You just need to use a different API</b> — for example, Ollama. It doesn\'t block your device, but registration with it may differ.\n\nDetailed instructions await you on the NumAI Plus GitHub page.\ngithub.com/gohoski/numAi\n</string>
